article.description: Sayeed Pridgett and Kendal Manuel scored 20 points apiece as Montana defeated North Dakota 77-70 on Friday night.
article.headline: Montana tops North Dakota 77-70
article.story: MISSOULA, Mont. -- Sayeed Pridgett and Kendal Manuel scored 20 points apiece as Montana defeated North Dakota 77-70 on Friday night. Timmy Falls had 15 points for Montana (4-5). Marlon Stewart had 19 points and eight assists for the Fighting Hawks (4-6). Filip Rebraca added 14 points and 12 rebounds. De'Sean Allen-Eikens had 13 points. Montana faces Oregon on the road next Wednesday. North Dakota faces Eastern Washington on the road on Sunday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
